criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Duration of SCI ≥1 year;

          -  Level of SCI C3-T1, AIS A & B;

          -  Age between 18 and 65 years.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Evidence of sympathetic integrity below the lesion level by the skin axon-reflex
             vasodilatation (SkARV) test;

          -  Known allergies to midodrine hydrochloride;

          -  PMH of diagnosed heart, kidney, peripheral vascular, or cerebral vascular disease, or
             diabetes mellitus;

          -  Hypertension (BP>140/90 mmHg);

          -  Untreated thyroid disease;

          -  Acute illness or infection;

          -  Current smoker;

          -  Pregnancy.
